Merge pull request #52 from mozilla/connectAnotherDevice-to-25-percent r=self, vladikoff

Remove connectAnotherDevice from the `verification` experiments. Place
50% of users into the `connectAnotherDevice` experiment, ignoring `isMetricsEnabledValue`. 25% of users will go into each of the two buckets, compared to 1.25% now.

I'm self-merging after input from vladikoff w/o further review. I'll take responsibility for any blowups.
fix(experiments): subject safety++

feat(experiments): Pass in a reference to able to the verification experiemnts.

This allows each experiment to query able itself to determine whether it's
the active experiment, which results in *much* cleaner frontend code.

Now the frontend no longer needs to track which experiments are mutually
exclusive, it just runs through a list of possible experiments and sees
which are active.

Goes with https://github.com/mozilla/fxa-content-server/pull/4673
